cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

The paper proposes a supervised online hashing method for image retrieval, which involves learning binary codes based on pairwise similarities of training instances. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel approach to model the similarity distributions between the input data and the hashing codes, which involves solving the challenging initialization problem and minimizing the Kullback-Leibler divergence. These techniques are related to machine learning and optimization, which suggest that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed method on three widely-used benchmarks for image retrieval, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
